## Approach: Divide and Conquer

Pair up lists and merge each pair. Repeat until only one list remains. Each merge of two sorted lists is O(n). This halves the number of lists each round, giving O(N log k) total.

```javascript
function mergeKSortedLists(lists) {
  if (!lists.length) return [];
  function merge(a, b) {
    const result = [];
    let i = 0, j = 0;
    while (i < a.length && j < b.length)
      result.push(a[i] <= b[j] ? a[i++] : b[j++]);
    return result.concat(a.slice(i), b.slice(j));
  }
  while (lists.length > 1) {
    const merged = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < lists.length; i += 2)
      merged.push(i+1 < lists.length ? merge(lists[i], lists[i+1]) : lists[i]);
    lists = merged;
  }
  return lists[0];
}
```

**Time Complexity:** O(N log k) where N is total elements

**Space Complexity:** O(N)

